00:36:05.600 --> 00:36:06.780
RETO MEIER: Yes.

00:36:06.780 --> 00:36:08.240
IAN NI-LEWIS: And it has
an up affordance.

00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:08.940
RETO MEIER: Yes.

00:36:08.940 --> 00:36:11.560
IAN NI-LEWIS: But it has
also a Done button.

00:36:11.560 --> 00:36:13.350
RETO MEIER: Yes.

00:36:13.350 --> 00:36:14.740
IAN NI-LEWIS: Do they both
do the same thing?

00:36:14.740 --> 00:36:14.970
RETO MEIER: No.

00:36:14.970 --> 00:36:17.490
So if you hit the up affordance,
it goes back.

00:36:17.490 --> 00:36:18.590
And that's kind of
important here.

00:36:18.590 --> 00:36:22.900
So up, in terms of Android,
means, don't go to a sibling,

00:36:22.900 --> 00:36:24.180
go to a parent.

00:36:24.180 --> 00:36:27.050
Now basically, what you're
going through here is a

00:36:27.050 --> 00:36:29.910
wizard, and a wizard is a
horizontal sibling flow.

00:36:29.910 --> 00:36:33.110
You're moving from equal
stages along the path.

00:36:33.110 --> 00:36:34.930
So Back should take you back.

00:36:34.930 --> 00:36:37.080
Up should take you out
of this workflow.

00:36:37.080 --> 00:36:38.430
And in this case, it's
basically the

00:36:38.430 --> 00:36:39.860
equivalent of cancel.

00:36:39.860 --> 00:36:41.900
So you probably don't actually
want to do an

00:36:41.900 --> 00:36:42.450
up affordance here.

00:36:42.450 --> 00:36:45.120
You want to have basically
a Save and Write.

00:36:45.120 --> 00:36:48.815
Or I can't remember the name
that Roman has been using for

00:36:48.815 --> 00:36:52.470
it, but the alternative way, you
basically have a Save and

00:36:52.470 --> 00:36:54.040
a Cancel right at
the top here.

00:36:54.040 --> 00:36:55.600
So those are the two things
that you can do.

00:36:55.600 --> 00:36:57.040
IAN NI-LEWIS: A commit
type of thing.

00:36:57.040 --> 00:36:57.590
RETO MEIER: Yeah, exactly.

00:36:57.590 --> 00:36:59.110
Like a Commit or Cancel
at any point.

00:36:59.110 --> 00:36:59.570
IAN NI-LEWIS: Right.

00:36:59.570 --> 00:37:03.910
And in general, if you're going
to do a wizard, the very

00:37:03.910 --> 00:37:06.190
best way to do it that
users like is to

00:37:06.190 --> 00:37:08.880
just use a view pager.

00:37:08.880 --> 00:37:14.100
Because it is weird to have
a verb in your action bar.

00:37:14.100 --> 00:37:14.380
RETO MEIER: In your title bar.

00:37:14.380 --> 00:37:16.550
IAN NI-LEWIS: Yeah,
in your title bar.

00:37:16.550 --> 00:37:20.120
But having that as a particular
tab on a wizard,

00:37:20.120 --> 00:37:23.010
especially a wizard that you
can swipe through, which is

00:37:23.010 --> 00:37:26.790
becoming a far more interesting
and understood

00:37:26.790 --> 00:37:29.290
action than a Back
button, honestly.

00:37:29.290 --> 00:37:30.830
I mean, you'd think a Back
button is the easiest

00:37:30.830 --> 00:37:31.400
thing in the world.

00:37:31.400 --> 00:37:31.680
RETO MEIER: Yeah.

00:37:31.680 --> 00:37:33.380
IAN NI-LEWIS: But I've seen
people with a Back button

00:37:33.380 --> 00:37:35.290
right there trying to swipe.

