00:38:58.810 --> 00:39:01.210
The disadvantage here, of
course, is that you have to be

00:39:01.210 --> 00:39:01.800
conscious of it.

00:39:01.800 --> 00:39:04.030
You have to have a tag
in the right place.

00:39:04.030 --> 00:39:06.910
You have to manually do the
tapping rather than just

00:39:06.910 --> 00:39:08.210
having it automatically.

00:39:08.210 --> 00:39:11.200
The advantage is that you
don't need to have any

00:39:11.200 --> 00:39:11.760
services running.

00:39:11.760 --> 00:39:13.380
It's really efficient.

00:39:13.380 --> 00:39:14.790
Nothing needs to be running
in the background.

00:39:14.790 --> 00:39:16.620
The app can be completely
gone.

00:39:16.620 --> 00:39:19.720
And once you hit an NFC tag,
it's still going to wake up

00:39:19.720 --> 00:39:23.400
